      </list>
      <p>Unlike the ASFR and GFR, to produce the standard error and the other precision indicators for the TFR, the JK argument should be declared as JK = "Yes" so that the Jackknife repeated replication method will be used to estimate the standard error, as below. Note that in addition to the standard output, the function produces the number of Jackknife replicates as the number of iterations reported below.</p>
      <list list-type="simple">
        <list-item>
          <p>
            <monospace>&gt; fert(ZWIR71,Indicator = "tfr", JK = "Yes")</monospace>
          </p>
        </list-item>
        <list-item>
          <p>
            <monospace>The current function calculated TFR based on a reference period of 36 months</monospace>
          </p>
        </list-item>
