          </p>
        </list-item>
        <list-item>
          <p>
            <monospace>The average reference period is 2015.33</monospace>
          </p>
        </list-item>
        <list-item>
          <p>
            <monospace>    TFR     N    WN</monospace>
          </p>
        </list-item>
        <list-item>
          <p>
            <monospace>[1,] 2.554 28964 28933</monospace>
          </p>
        </list-item>
      </list>
      <p>All the functions above can be used in case of data for ever-married women. In the example below, the TFR is calculated based on the ever-married women 2014 Bangladesh DHS (BDHS) by declaring the <monospace>EverMW = "Yes"</monospace> argument.</p>
      <list list-type="simple">
        <list-item>
          <p>
            <monospace>&gt; BDIR72 &lt;- read_dta("C:/………/BDIR72FL.DTA")</monospace>
          </p>
        </list-item>
