        <p>Similar to the <monospace>fert</monospace> function, several arguments can be used in the <monospace>chmort</monospace> function to declare variables with names other than the standard names used in the DHS surveys, such as <monospace>Strata, Cluster, Weight, Date_of_interview, Date_of_birth,</monospace> and <monospace>Age_at_death</monospace>. Also, arguments like <monospace>CL, Class, Period,</monospace> and <monospace>PeriodEnd</monospace> can be used in the <monospace>chmort</monospace> function to produce subnational rates and rates based on different reference periods and with a non-default 99% confidence interval, as below.</p>
